          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Online safety tips\nYou can help protect your Credit Card from fraud happening to you just by following some basic practices. These safety tips will help you protect your credit whether shopping online or travelling.\nCarefully read privacy and security documents before you buy.\nPrint/save confirmations of your transactions and keep them. Never provide your Credit Card number via email.\nIf you suspect your Card number has been mishandled, report it to your Credit Card issuer right away.\nOnly make a purchase from reputable sites.\nCheck for signs that the site is secure. Look for a closed padlock on your browser\u2019s address bar or a URL address that begins with shttp or https.",
